corrections/opinions: 1 - the miniled/oled graphics thing. (already mentioned by others) 2 - you said for the 96w power adaptor it was ¬£70 extra, when the video [2:02] clearly says ¬£79. 3 - the mba speed graphics [8:30] shows it has much faster write than read speeds - 50% faster! i've never seen storage that is much faster write than read (if at all). if it's true, then my bad. 4 - the position of the two laptops keeps changing in the video. for the viewer, sometime the mbp m5 is on the left and then it cuts to another scene where the mbp m5 is now on the right, and then it cuts to another scene, where it's back on the left, etc. keep some consistency please - just so the viewer doesn't get confused which way round they are, especially when there's suddenly spec graphics/text on them. 5 - you are using way more expensive models that the base models. e.g. having 1tb storage each, 32gb ram in the mbp, mbp nano-texture, etc. but then you casually say to the viewer [8:42] ¬£1k for the mba and ¬£1.6k for the mbp. that's the base model prices, not the ones you're showing/using. it's always worth telling the viewer the cost of the macbooks you're actually using as well, so they don't think they can get all the stuff/specs you were showing for the last 8 minutes for just ¬£1k or ¬£1.6k. that should be much clearer. feels like a bit of a rush job video without the usual quality checks beforehand. otherwise, keep up the good work. thanks.

something nobody talks about and they really should in reviews is not just brightness, but color depth, no matter how well calibrated an oled panel is or how bright it gets, if it is 8 bit it definitely looks worse than a 10 bit or 10 bit + frc panel (10+2), i am using an a56 and i came from a redmi note 13 pro 5g and the screen is honestly much worse, no matter which color mode i set it to it is simply inferior, colors look more washed out and it looks worse overall, the system is excellent but it is way less enjoyable, xiaomi does not only offer good processors, it offers excellent displays, there are almost no other brands at these prices selling 10 bit + frc panels, they are completely worth it, this is not just an extra, it is something you are looking at all the time, it used to be a feature exclusive to the high end, now that 120hz is standard they should focus more on highlighting color depth, pwm, dc dimming, and not just hdr brightness which is mostly marketing, the more important thing is hbm because if it is high enough it looks good under the sun and it usually also indicates that sdr performance is good too
